wikipedia_page.main: Dennis Warrior (birth registered second ¼ 1922) is an English former professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1940s and 1950s. He played at club level for Leeds, Castleford (Heritage № 213 as a wartime guest) and Bramley as a centre, i.e. number 3 or 4.
